==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Portionist
<hw>Por"tion*ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
scholar at Merton College, Oxford, who has a certain academical
allowance or portion; -- corrupted into <xex>postmaster</xex>.</def>
<rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>One of the incumbents of a
benefice which has two or more rectors or vicars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portionless</ent>⟦br⟧
